Pablo doesn't.

44
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:50,164
Berna. G0 get the car.

45
00:03:59,320 --> 00:04:00,765
[Judy sighs]

46
00:04:01,920 --> 00:04:04,161
Are you going to give me a cigarette
or what?

47
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:18,646
Mmm.

48
00:04:21,280 --> 00:04:22,361
Well...

49
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:28,362
we really want you to realize, Agent Pefia,

50
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:32,126
the potential of what we're offering you.
Mmm?

51
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:38,967
Because, well...
with all the information in the world,

52
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:41,202
you still have to be a policeman, right?

53
00:04:45,280 --> 00:04:49,126
I know what it feels like
when Pablo kills someone close to you.

54
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:53,920
What's that?

55
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:56,801
Information that would be
very valuable to you.

56
00:04:57,600 --> 00:05:00,046
That was very easy for us to find.
Take it.

57
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:09,686
She's staying with a friend.
That little girl, Maritza.

58
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:13,048
The woman that betrayed you
and got Carrillo killed.

59
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:14,531
You'll find her there.

60
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:21,846
I told you we have an enemy in common.

61
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:28,810
[vehicle approaches, stops]

62
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:32,690
If you change your mind, give us a ring.

63
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:50,649
[Latin guitar theme music plays]

64
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:25,571
[sighs]

65
00:07:25,640 --> 00:07:27,881
<i>[Steve]
Life goes on, right?</i>

66
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:32,769
<i>And for Escobar,
that was</i> a <i>pretty good thing.</i>

67
00:07:32,840 --> 00:07:36,561
<i>He remained at large,
protected by an army of sicarios...</i>

68
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:40,090
<i>in</i> a <i>city that refused to give him up.</i>

69
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:43,805
<i>Pablo kept his lawyers working overtime...</i>

70
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:49,441
<i>continuing to negotiate his surrender
with Colombian Attorney General De Greiff.</i>

71
00:07:50,320 --> 00:07:52,243
<i>But it was bullshit.</i>

72
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:55,051
<i>Why surrender when
you're holding all the cards?</i>

73
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:59,163
<i>He was free. And business was booming.</i>

74
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:00,765
LEADER OF THE SEARCH BLOC KILLED

75
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:03,650
<i>For those of us tasked
with catching Escobar,</i>

76
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:05,722
<i>Carrillo 's death was</i> a <i>punch in the gut.</i>

77
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:09,930
