95
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:19,403
If I dive in there,
I'd splash all the water out of the pool.

96
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:26,564
Sir, Fernando Duque is here.

97
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:30,688
And you...
And what are you doing, my little love?

98
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:34,526
That's it. Little kicks, little kicks.
Like a little pair of scissors.

99
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:36,568
That's right, like a little puppy.

100
00:09:36,680 --> 00:09:38,170
That's it, beautiful.

101
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:40,850
Hey, ladies.

102
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:46,491
My kids are in the pool.
Does someone know how to swim?

103
00:09:46,560 --> 00:09:49,803
- Yeah, boss, they call me "Flipper."
- Flipper?

104
00:09:49,880 --> 00:09:54,010
You talk so much shit, Blackie. You'd sink
like a rock tied to a heavier rock.

105
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:55,445
Eat shit, Velasco.

106
00:09:55,520 --> 00:09:57,887
- Velasco, I'm putting my trust in you.
- Yes, sir.

107
00:09:57,960 --> 00:09:59,166
Not in Flipper.

108
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:01,806
[Pablo] Flipper.

109
00:10:03,160 --> 00:10:05,891
[chuckles] "They call me Flipper."

110
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:11,082
[sports chatter over radio]

111
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:12,764
- What's the score'?
- Two to zero.

112
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:15,087
The National team is winning.
We're killing them!

113
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:16,924
[Pablo] That's it!

114
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:21,364
[upbeat Latin music playing on radio]

115
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:37,123
Careful with that little dance.
You're starting to put ideas in my head.

116
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:40,407
Love, who is picking up Carlos?

117
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:43,484
La Quica. He's on his way.

118
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:47,329
Hey, that smells good.

119
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:51,644
[chuckles]
Pablo, the kids love this place.

120
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:53,722
- It's nice, isn't it?
- Yes.

121
00:11:12,040 --> 00:11:13,690
[in Spanish]
On your feet. Now!

122
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:19,084
I didn't know. I didn't know, I swear.
Limén lied to me.

123
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:23,923
N0, please. When they find me,
they're going to kill me.

124
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:25,764
- No! No!
- Stay still!

125
00:11:26,640 --> 00:11:27,926
Please.

126
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:32,170
Do you think I wanted this?

127
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:35,727
They used me
and they're throwing my life away.

128
00:11:36,400 --> 00:11:38,767
[in English]
You're breaking my fucking heart, baby.

129
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:44,368
[in Spanish]
You're all the same.

130
00:11:44,440 --> 00:11:47,410
You don't listen. Nobody listens!

131
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:50,844
And all those people dying for no reason.

132
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:58,045
What's up, Pefia?
What should we do with her?

133
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:06,650
- [Connie speaks indistinctly]
- [in English] She's good with kids.

134
00:12:12,160 --> 00:12:14,367
I'm so sorry for your loss, Mrs. Carrillo.

135
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:25,284
I keep wondering
if it's better to know the truth.

136
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:29,006
I don't follow.

137
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:35,282
The things they said about my husband,
about what he did before he was killed.

138
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:38,402
Did he shoot a child?

139
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:43,287
Did he kill that boy
like they said on the news?

140
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:48,440
N0. Absolutely not.

141
00:12:50,560 --> 00:12:55,407
Your husband did everything in his means
to get Escobar.

142
00:12:56,800 --> 00:12:58,768
But he did not cross the line.

143
00:13:07,360 --> 00:13:08,850
Well, that was rough.

144
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:16,247
- I just kept looking at her, thinking...
- Hey.

145
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:20,844
It's not gonna happen to me,
it's not gonna happen to us.

146
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:25,243
You want me to come home?

147
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:33,849
Just make sure you're still you
when it's all over.

148
00:13:41,040 --> 00:13:44,328
So three years in the jungles
fighting FARC.

149
00:13:45,280 --> 00:13:49,649
Hugo Martinez chose his own path
a long time ago

150
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:51,882
and he hasn't deviated from it since.

151
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:57,441
He's methodical, favors procedure
and strict protocol.

152
00:13:57,520 --> 00:13:59,249
Do you think you can get him to do it?

153
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:06,284
<i>[Steve] How do you get</i> a <i>man to take</i> a <i>job
that nobody wants? Don't get</i> me <i>wrong.</i>

154
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:09,603
<i>There was no shortage of brave men
in the Colombian National Police.</i>

155
00:14:09,680 --> 00:14:13,765
<i>But signing up to replace Carrillo
as the head of the Search Bloc</i>

156
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:16,081
<i>would take</i> a <i>lot more than bravery.</i>

157
00:14:16,160 --> 00:14:19,642
<i>Gaviria couldn't count on someone
raising their hand.</i>

158
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:23,805
<i>It would take</i> a <i>certain kind of pressure
to find the right volunteer.</i>

159
00:14:23,880 --> 00:14:25,644
[in Spanish]
ls that your father?

160
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:27,808
Over there with the president?

161
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:34,405
That's cool.

162
00:14:37,040 --> 00:14:39,202
[applause]

163
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:48,322
To all those present,
it is my honor to present

164
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:51,643
the President of the Republic...

165
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:58,529
His Excellency,
Don César Augusto Gaviria Trujillo.

166
00:14:58,600 --> 00:15:00,921
[applause]

167
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:09,369
[Gaviria]
Congratulations, Class of 1992.

168
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:12,643
Recent events...

169
00:15:14,160 --> 00:15:17,130
contrast heavily with today's ceremony.

170
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:24,406
Each one of you has decided to sacrifice
your personal interests...

171
00:15:25,160 --> 00:15:30,041
and dedicate your lives
to the service of the nation.

172
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:35,169
There is no higher honor...

173
00:15:37,360 --> 00:15:39,328
than to serve your homeland.

174
00:15:39,400 --> 00:15:42,483
[band plays up-tempo patriotic music]

175
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:50,048
- Colonel, how are you doing?
- Very well.

176
00:15:50,120 --> 00:15:52,487
I enjoyed your speech very much,
Mr. President.

177
00:15:52,560 --> 00:15:54,881
I'm glad. It was also for you.

178
00:15:56,640 --> 00:16:02,249
Look, Colonel, in the last 24 hours,
I've been discussing with my advisors

179
00:16:02,320 --> 00:16:05,051
who should be at the head
of the Search Bloc.

180
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:08,007
They mentioned many names.

181
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:11,570
But I would like it to be you,
Colonel Martinez.

182
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:16,686
That's an honor, Mr. President,
but at this point in my career,

183
00:16:16,760 --> 00:16:21,926
- l'm sure you can find a better candidate.
- Colombia wants to end this nightmare.

184
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:25,645
And I know you're the man to do it.

185
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:29,330
The nation deserves someone
better than me.

186
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:36,371
Your son was one of the best
in the academy. He's an excellent cadet.

187
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:38,761
He worked very hard.
I'm very proud of him.

188
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:44,722
We asked the best in the class
to join the Search Bloc.

189
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,843
And your son happily accepted.

190
00:16:50,360 --> 00:16:53,045
I ask that you at least
consider my request.

191
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:56,724
For Colombia.

192
00:17:00,160 --> 00:17:02,128
[crowd applauds]

193
00:17:07,280 --> 00:17:10,011
[upbeat Latin music plays on radio]

194
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,964
- Carlos!
- Tata!

195
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:23,287
Come on, come on. Let's see.

196
00:17:24,120 --> 00:17:25,565
Go ahead.

197
00:17:25,640 --> 00:17:29,087
- I can't believe it. Look at you.
- Slowly, slowly.

198
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:31,811
I don't want any more visits
to the doctor.

199
00:17:31,880 --> 00:17:35,885
- Manuela, you're so beautiful. Look at me.
- Look how tan he is.

200
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:38,725
- [chuckles]
- He looks like a movie star, right?

201
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:39,961
Yes, boss.

202
00:17:40,040 --> 00:17:42,088
- He looks like Tom Cruise.
- Well...

203
00:17:42,160 --> 00:17:43,366
[Carlos]
Look at her, Pablo.

204
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:46,330
I can't believe you brought me from Miami
to see my sister like this.

205
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:49,563
No. I'm just so happy to see you.

206
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:53,843
Oh, my God. Carlos!

207
00:17:55,400 --> 00:17:58,768
Welcome, sweetie.
I'm so happy to have you home.

208
00:17:59,480 --> 00:18:02,609
Tonight, I am going to make
the best meal this family has ever had.

209
00:18:03,280 --> 00:18:06,727
Well, then...
ready to go for a little walk?

210
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:10,843
[Carlos] It's incredible how much
the children have grown, Pablo.

211
00:18:10,920 --> 00:18:13,730
Manuelita is a princess. She is beautiful.

212
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:17,725
She's the one who controls everything
around here. ljust pay the bills.

213
00:18:19,280 --> 00:18:20,805
I heard about Carrillo.

214
00:18:21,720 --> 00:18:25,247
If that son of a bitch was still alive,
many more policemen would have died.

215
00:18:25,320 --> 00:18:29,291
I did the police a favor. Believe me.

216
00:18:29,360 --> 00:18:32,284
Do you think the police agree with you?

217
00:18:32,360 --> 00:18:36,649
No one wants war, Carlos.
Especially when they know they would lose.

218
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:39,325
But all that's in the past.

219
00:18:40,040 --> 00:18:45,809
And I'm ready to get back to business.
I'm all in.

220
00:18:45,880 --> 00:18:49,282
- Tell me about Miami.
- What can I tell you, Pablo?

221
00:18:49,360 --> 00:18:53,081
The demand keeps increasing
and the merchandise keeps on coming.

222
00:18:53,160 --> 00:18:56,084
Business hasn't been affected
by what happened at La Catedral,

223
00:18:56,160 --> 00:18:57,810
nor by what you did.

224
00:18:59,360 --> 00:19:02,603
Well, business can always
get better, right?

225
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:06,047
<i>[Steve]
Business was pretty good.</i>

226
00:19:06,120 --> 00:19:09,886
<i>And a large part of that
was due to a guy they called the Lion.</i>

227
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:12,321
<i>You might remember him
as</i> a <i>Medellin hustler</i>

228
00:19:12,400 --> 00:19:17,361
<i>who used to stuff bricks of cocaine into
his jacket and smuggled them into Miami.</i>

229
00:19:17,440 --> 00:19:22,446
<i>Well, he stayed in Miami
and he</i> made <i>it his town.</i>

230
00:19:23,360 --> 00:19:25,010
[woman moans]

231
00:19:25,080 --> 00:19:27,526
<i>[Steve]
He was responsible for</i> a <i>smuggling network</i>

232
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:31,366
<i>that brought in Pablo 's cocaine
by the ton. He was great at it.</i>

233
00:19:32,720 --> 00:19:35,929
<i>But getting cocaine into the States
wasn't really the problem.</i>

234
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:39,930
<i>The prob/em was,
what do you do with all that money?</i>

235
00:19:40,640 --> 00:19:44,770
<i>Sure, some of it could stay in the States.
And the narcos did that.</i>

236
00:19:44,840 --> 00:19:49,402
<i>They bought crooked banks,
real estate, car dealerships,</i>

237
00:19:49,480 --> 00:19:52,006
<i>race horses, an', you name it.</i>

238
00:19:52,800 --> 00:19:57,522
<i>But if you're gonna run</i> a <i>cocaine empire,
you need to have</i> a <i>lot of cash on hand.</i>

239
00:19:57,600 --> 00:20:00,888
<i>And getting cash back into Colombia
wasn't easy.</i>

240
00:20:02,280 --> 00:20:03,566
<i>Let</i> me <i>put it this way:</i>

241
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:06,202
<i>This is what</i> a <i>ton of cocaine looks like.</i>

242
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:12,330
<i>And here's what the same ton of cocaine
looks like when it's converted into cash.</i>

243
00:20:12,440 --> 00:20:13,487
<i>See the prob/em?</i>

244
00:20:14,560 --> 00:20:17,962
<i>Lion had to be creative
with how he got that money to Pablo.</i>

245
00:20:19,120 --> 00:20:22,363
<i>And he was.
His shipments showed up like clockwork.</i>

246
00:20:25,320 --> 00:20:28,244
<i>But the deeper Pablo went into his war
with the government...</i>

247
00:20:30,040 --> 00:20:32,281
<i>the more important these shipments were.</i>

248
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:35,521
<i>Pablo needed more money than ever.</i>

249
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:38,171
<i>Without it, he was fucked.</i>

250
00:20:39,120 --> 00:20:41,407
[in Spanish]
Let's bring the Lion over here.

251
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:45,810
I want to speak to him face to face,
like the old days.

252
00:20:45,880 --> 00:20:48,486
- Okay.
- Make some new arrangements.

253
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:50,284
Some better ones.

254
00:20:51,280 --> 00:20:52,327
Quica.

255
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:57,482
Give Velasco a call.
Tell him to find the Lion.

256
00:20:57,560 --> 00:21:00,006
Carlos and I want to speak to him
about business.

257
00:21:02,960 --> 00:21:06,442
It's time to get back
to making money, brother.

258
00:21:06,520 --> 00:21:08,887
- Like the good old days, Pablo.
- Exactly.

259
00:21:21,360 --> 00:21:22,930
What's up, Maritza?

260
00:21:24,240 --> 00:21:25,366
What happened?

261
00:21:27,440 --> 00:21:32,002
The police are looking for me.
They want to put a bullet in my head.

262
00:21:32,080 --> 00:21:35,926
I'm sorry, Maritza. lthought
something good would come from all this.

263
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:37,490
Something good?

264
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:39,481
[scoffs]

265
00:21:42,480 --> 00:21:44,244
Let me come work with you.

266
00:21:44,960 --> 00:21:46,883
No, Maritza, you're crazy.

267
00:21:46,960 --> 00:21:48,689
[phone rings]

268
00:21:49,840 --> 00:21:51,649
I have to get this.

269
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:53,085
Give me one second.

270
00:21:56,480 --> 00:21:57,561
What's up?

271
00:21:57,640 --> 00:22:02,089
Where the fuck are you, Limon? Think you
can make me wait around for you, bitch?

272
00:22:02,160 --> 00:22:04,288
I'm close by, man.

273
00:22:04,360 --> 00:22:07,887
I mean, there's a lot of goddamn traffic,
but I'm on my way.

274
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:11,681
<i>I don't give</i> a <i>fuck if there's traffic.
I need you here now!</i>

275
00:22:11,760 --> 00:22:15,446
You have to take this shit with you,
so get your ass over here. Right now.

276
00:22:15,560 --> 00:22:19,406
Yes, I know, I know.
Forgive me. I'm on my way.

277
00:22:31,560 --> 00:22:34,803
Maritza, I have to go.
I can't help you right now.

278
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:38,009
We already gave you money.
I'll call you later.

279
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:41,162
And we'll figure it out,
but I can't right now.

280
00:22:44,080 --> 00:22:45,605
[in English]
Okay, here we go.

281
00:22:47,480 --> 00:22:49,289
[engine starts]

282
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:50,524
[chatter in Spanish]

283
00:23:56,240 --> 00:23:58,163
[dialing phone]

284
00:24:00,040 --> 00:24:03,283
- [man in Spanish] Search <i>Bloc.</i>
- Lt's Pefia.

285
00:24:03,360 --> 00:24:07,081
I'm here with Trujillo at the corner
of 38th and 24th streets. We need back up.

286
00:24:07,160 --> 00:24:09,561
<i>Sorry, but there's no authorization
to dispatch patrols.</i>

287
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:14,089
We're watching one of Escobar's guys.
He just entered the building.

288
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:17,960
<i>Return to base with the location.
We can ask for authorization from Bogota'.</i>

289
00:24:19,320 --> 00:24:20,321
Sure.

290
00:24:21,240 --> 00:24:23,561
[mutters] And you'll show up next Tuesday,
son of a bitch.

291
00:24:27,520 --> 00:24:30,603
What time were you supposed to be here,
asshole?

292
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:34,002
You knew you had to make the delivery
before I pick up Lion tomorrow.

293
00:24:34,080 --> 00:24:36,606
No, brother, don't get mad.
It's just that...

294
00:24:36,680 --> 00:24:37,920
Limén!

295
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:42,210
You're going to take this goddamn bag
and get out of here now! I'm watching you.

296
00:24:42,280 --> 00:24:44,009
- Calm down.
- Calm down?

297
00:24:44,080 --> 00:24:47,368
This is the last time you pull shit
like this, Limén. The last time!

298
00:24:50,680 --> 00:24:53,331
- This is the last time you make me wait.
- Come on, man...

299
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:56,688
- I told you. Get out of here.
- [in English] Oh, shit. That's Velasco.

300
00:24:56,760 --> 00:24:59,650
[in Spanish]
Shit. What do we do?

301
00:24:59,720 --> 00:25:02,326
We stick with Velasco.
The other one doesn't matter.

302
00:25:03,760 --> 00:25:05,922
How many guys do you think are inside,
Pefia?

303
00:25:07,720 --> 00:25:09,609
Too many forjust us two, no?

304
00:25:09,680 --> 00:25:12,524
Yeah. We'd be screwed.

305
00:25:13,800 --> 00:25:17,202
Son of a bitch.
We should call for backup, right?

306
00:25:21,320 --> 00:25:22,685
[dials phone]

307
00:25:23,640 --> 00:25:26,211
- Who are you calling?
- [line ringing]

308
00:25:49,520 --> 00:25:52,729
- [Trujillo] What's going on, Pefia?
- L'll handle this.

309
00:26:05,080 --> 00:26:08,971
[Javier]
This is Trujillo. You can trust him.

310
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:12,604
You're finally seeing the light.

311
00:26:13,400 --> 00:26:16,290
Let's just see if this works.

312
00:26:18,360 --> 00:26:19,850
You two coming'?

313
00:26:22,960 --> 00:26:26,885
Okay, then. You two, in the front with me.

314
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:29,964
Berna, with his men, around back.
Understood?

315
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:33,883
Just stay clear of the windows.

316
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:36,088
- Let's go, then.
- [Carlos] Let's move.

317
00:27:32,920 --> 00:27:35,207
[automatic gunfire nearby]

318
00:27:35,280 --> 00:27:36,645
[men shouting]

319
00:27:48,600 --> 00:27:50,170
[man whimpering]

320
00:27:56,480 --> 00:27:57,606
[man grunts]

321
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:02,843
- They're everywhere.
- Let's go down.

322
00:28:25,960 --> 00:28:27,166
Hey!

323
00:28:47,520 --> 00:28:48,520
[door opens]

324
00:28:57,280 --> 00:28:58,441
[gunfire]

325
00:29:16,320 --> 00:29:17,320
[9 Fu nts]

326
00:29:21,400 --> 00:29:24,483
Where were you going,
you filthy son of a bitch? Huh?

327
00:29:27,720 --> 00:29:29,165
[9 Fu nts]

328
00:29:34,800 --> 00:29:37,007
[Latin music plays softly on radio]

329
00:29:38,320 --> 00:29:40,163
Here it is, Mrs. Escobar.

330
00:29:41,640 --> 00:29:44,325
- What's that?
- Lt's a delivery.

331
00:29:44,400 --> 00:29:47,006
- But who told you to buy this?
- It was me.

332
00:29:48,320 --> 00:29:49,924
It's some clothes.

333
00:29:51,040 --> 00:29:52,087
Hermilda.

334
00:29:53,760 --> 00:29:57,162
Hermilda, for God's sake...
you can't send him out with so much money.

335
00:29:57,240 --> 00:29:59,846
- Oh, Tata!
- They are going to know where we are.

336
00:29:59,920 --> 00:30:01,968
You worry too much.

337
00:30:03,320 --> 00:30:07,291
It's going to affect the children. Do you
want Juan Pablo and Manuela to worry?

338
00:30:11,560 --> 00:30:12,891
You're right.

339
00:30:17,040 --> 00:30:19,122
When Pablo was a little boy...

340
00:30:21,760 --> 00:30:25,162
he came home from school one day,
very angry.

341
00:30:27,280 --> 00:30:30,523
A little girl made fun of his shoes.

342
00:30:32,200 --> 00:30:34,123
They were ragged.

343
00:30:34,920 --> 00:30:38,003
And we didn't have any money
to buy him new ones.

344
00:30:38,080 --> 00:30:43,484
But that night, I went into town
and I stole a pair from a store.

345
00:30:43,560 --> 00:30:45,961
The next day, Pablo went back to school.

346
00:30:50,840 --> 00:30:55,164
Being poor is not an excuse
to look like you are.

347
00:30:57,640 --> 00:31:00,689
You've always just taken
what you wanted, right?

348
00:31:00,760 --> 00:31:02,524
And Pablo as well.

349
00:31:05,800 --> 00:31:07,211
[in English]
Mr. Ambassador,

350
00:31:07,280 --> 00:31:11,046
I believe people fall
into two categories, basically:

351
00:31:11,120 --> 00:31:12,531
those who rely on hope...

352
00:31:13,960 --> 00:31:16,247
and those who rely on faith,

353
00:31:16,320 --> 00:31:20,530
who see a system at work in the world
and are devoted to it.

354
00:31:21,160 --> 00:31:26,485
It may be religion,
but in the case of police work, a method.

355
00:31:27,160 --> 00:31:30,369
I'm guessing that you fall
on the faith side.

356
00:31:30,440 --> 00:31:31,646
Correct.

357
00:31:32,440 --> 00:31:35,250
We can catch Escobar
in any number of ways.

358
00:31:35,320 --> 00:31:39,848
But if the one we choose
furthers an already strained relationship

359
00:31:39,960 --> 00:31:42,770
between the Colombian people
and its police,

360
00:31:42,840 --> 00:31:47,084
a strain caused by
years of corruption and abuse,

361
00:31:47,160 --> 00:31:48,810
then we'll have lost.

362
00:31:48,880 --> 00:31:50,325
Even if we catch him.

363
00:31:50,960 --> 00:31:53,725
Your philosophy is our philosophy,
Colonel.

364
00:31:54,360 --> 00:31:56,647
Yeah, we'll see about that.

365
00:31:56,720 --> 00:31:57,926
Thank you very much.

366
00:31:59,680 --> 00:32:02,286
- [Crosby] Good to sit down with you.
- Mr. Ambassador,

367
00:32:02,360 --> 00:32:05,091
the whole world is watching
how we handle this.

368
00:32:05,880 --> 00:32:10,681
I won't allow it to be corrupted
by outside interests or darker instincts.

369
00:32:25,040 --> 00:32:26,280
[in Spanish]
It worked.

370
00:32:27,400 --> 00:32:29,004
We're even.

371
00:32:30,080 --> 00:32:34,324
I need you to help me get a visa
and get my family out of Medellin.

372
00:32:34,400 --> 00:32:36,607
Somewhere Pablo can't find us.

373
00:32:38,240 --> 00:32:40,004
It doesn't work like that.

374
00:32:40,880 --> 00:32:41,961
I'm sorry.

375
00:32:42,600 --> 00:32:44,170
So, then...?

376
00:32:45,160 --> 00:32:47,162
How am I supposed to be okay?

377
00:33:15,120 --> 00:33:18,010
Is this how things are going to work
from now on, Pena?

378
00:33:19,360 --> 00:33:23,331
Don't worry about it, okay?
It won't happen again.

379
00:33:24,240 --> 00:33:28,006
- No. I'm not worried.
- [starts engine]

380
00:33:38,600 --> 00:33:40,011
[Don Berna]
Leave us.

381
00:33:47,480 --> 00:33:49,403
Life's funny, Velasco.

382
00:33:50,440 --> 00:33:53,489
This could easily
have ended up in reverse.

383
00:33:54,520 --> 00:33:59,401
Me lying there,
you and your men ready to torture me.

384
00:34:01,080 --> 00:34:03,162
Look how everything's changed.

385
00:34:15,680 --> 00:34:18,206
We are both loyal soldiers.

386
00:34:22,560 --> 00:34:25,325
Serving our generals.

387
00:34:26,760 --> 00:34:28,569
But you know what?

388
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:32,886
When it's time to give up your boss...

389
00:34:33,560 --> 00:34:36,848
[grunts, breathing heavily]

390
00:34:36,920 --> 00:34:39,127
we give up our boss.

391
00:34:39,200 --> 00:34:41,885
[screaming]

392
00:34:47,040 --> 00:34:51,489
Ma'am, nothing about Pablo, but...
he gave up this.

393
00:35:00,440 --> 00:35:05,082
- Three of his accountants.
- And their addresses.

394
00:35:05,160 --> 00:35:09,131
He also told me Pablo
still has a large army and a lot of money.

395
00:35:09,200 --> 00:35:12,807
Yes, but that could be complete bullshit,
no? To scare us off.

396
00:35:14,560 --> 00:35:18,201
Or it could be true. To scare us off.

397
00:35:23,400 --> 00:35:24,526
[sighs]

398
00:35:25,840 --> 00:35:27,649
There lies the key.

399
00:35:28,360 --> 00:35:32,081
If we leave him without money,
we leave him without an army.

400
00:35:32,920 --> 00:35:34,285
Something else.

401
00:35:34,400 --> 00:35:36,528
Velasco was going to the airport tomorrow

402
00:35:36,600 --> 00:35:39,570
because the Lion will be arriving
in the afternoon from Miami.

403
00:35:43,960 --> 00:35:46,008
[people chuckling, chattering nearby]

404
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:50,609
Excuse me, sir. It's Judy Moncada.

405
00:35:59,320 --> 00:36:00,845
Mrs. Moncada.

406
00:36:02,360 --> 00:36:04,442
How can I help you?

407
00:36:21,600 --> 00:36:25,525
How was your trip? You must be beat.

408
00:36:25,600 --> 00:36:27,170
[in English]
Let's go. Get in.

409
00:36:27,240 --> 00:36:28,810
[in Spanish]
Where's Velasco?

410
00:36:37,200 --> 00:36:38,361
[whistles softly]

411
00:36:50,240 --> 00:36:51,571
There he is.

412
00:36:53,120 --> 00:36:54,360
Welcome.

413
00:36:55,600 --> 00:36:58,649
- Gilberto Rodriguez Orejuela.
- Lion.

414
00:36:59,600 --> 00:37:01,602
This is my brother, Miguel.

415
00:37:01,680 --> 00:37:04,365
And this gentleman is our associate,
Pacho Herrera.

416
00:37:04,440 --> 00:37:08,126
I'm very pleased to meet you, gentlemen.
It's a pleasure.

417
00:37:08,720 --> 00:37:11,405
Lion... May I call you that?

418
00:37:11,480 --> 00:37:15,371
- Yes, sir.
- Have a drink. Relax.

419
00:37:17,040 --> 00:37:19,850
They say, over there,
that you like whiskey.

420
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:25,291
Listen, gentlemen,
if I did something to offend you, or...

421
00:37:25,360 --> 00:37:30,924
What? Would we offer you a drink
if we were offended?

422
00:37:32,400 --> 00:37:33,481
Have a seat.

423
00:37:45,480 --> 00:37:47,323
Tell me something, Lion.

424
00:37:48,360 --> 00:37:50,966
D0 you like working for a thug?

425
00:37:58,040 --> 00:37:59,405
[Pablo] One...

426
00:37:59,480 --> 00:38:03,246
- two, three! [chuckles]
- [laughing]

427
00:38:03,320 --> 00:38:05,607
- Very good.
- [men murmuring]

428
00:38:05,720 --> 00:38:07,324
Good job.

429
00:38:07,400 --> 00:38:08,970
Look after your sister.

430
00:38:14,400 --> 00:38:15,811
What happened?

431
00:38:15,880 --> 00:38:17,530
[Blackie]
Hey, boss...

432
00:38:18,800 --> 00:38:21,007
Lion just called, sir.

433
00:38:21,080 --> 00:38:24,641
He said Velasco never showed up
at the airport, sir.

434
00:38:24,720 --> 00:38:28,725
Lion got scared shitless and left.
He took a plane back to Miami.

435
00:38:29,560 --> 00:38:33,326
Fucking Lion.
Is he a little bitch or what, brother?

436
00:38:33,400 --> 00:38:37,610
- And where is Velasco?
- Boss, I have no idea.

437
00:38:39,520 --> 00:38:41,648
Find him for me.

438
00:38:41,720 --> 00:38:43,643
Right away, boss.

439
00:38:48,280 --> 00:38:50,647
[upbeat Latin music plays on radio]

440
00:38:54,400 --> 00:38:59,088
- [Carlos] I can't believe you're cooking.
- But you know I always helped my mother.

441
00:38:59,160 --> 00:39:01,640
Uh-uh. I helped while you ate.

442
00:39:02,880 --> 00:39:04,086
[Carlos chuckles]

443
00:39:05,200 --> 00:39:09,762
You know, I'm very happy
that Pablo brought me here.

444
00:39:09,840 --> 00:39:11,808
But I'm worried about you.

445
00:39:11,880 --> 00:39:14,804
No. There's no reason to worry.

446
00:39:14,880 --> 00:39:16,689
For God's sake, Tata.

447
00:39:16,760 --> 00:39:19,843
Every cop in the country
is looking for Pablo.

448
00:39:20,480 --> 00:39:23,723
Every drug trafficker
who's not from Medellin wants him dead.

449
00:39:23,840 --> 00:39:27,322
And you're telling me there's no reason
to worry? Don't kid yourself.

450
00:39:29,320 --> 00:39:31,687
Today is a good day, Carlos.

451
00:39:31,760 --> 00:39:34,730
My family is all together. You're here.

452
00:39:38,960 --> 00:39:42,328
Pablo is a strong man.
He's always had to be.

453
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:45,401
There's no reason to change anything now.

454
00:39:56,920 --> 00:39:58,843
I hope you're hUTIQTY-

455
00:40:03,680 --> 00:40:05,091
[knocking]

456
00:40:12,680 --> 00:40:14,887
Come inside, I'm packing.

457
00:40:14,960 --> 00:40:17,486
Are you going to let me go to Medellin
or what?

458
00:40:18,320 --> 00:40:20,322
Is that why you accepted the job?

459
00:40:20,400 --> 00:40:22,687
You never should have volunteered.

460
00:40:22,760 --> 00:40:27,049
But you can't be reassigned now,
because it would end your career, right?

461
00:40:27,120 --> 00:40:29,851
Sure, only now I'm gonna be
"the boss's son."

462
00:40:29,920 --> 00:40:31,524
[sighs]

463
00:40:32,840 --> 00:40:35,525
It appears to me you don't understand
what's happening.

464
00:40:36,520 --> 00:40:39,330
I accepted because I wanted
to help my country.

465
00:40:41,280 --> 00:40:43,328
Come here, I want to show you something.

466
00:40:48,320 --> 00:40:50,607
I received this urn with my name.

467
00:40:54,360 --> 00:40:56,761
Look. On behalf of Pablo Escobar.

468
00:40:59,760 --> 00:41:01,569
It's an obituary.

469
00:41:03,720 --> 00:41:08,408
Look, son, you're going to do
exactly as I tell you.

470
00:41:08,480 --> 00:41:11,051
I'm going to make sure you survive this.
Understand?

471
00:41:17,520 --> 00:41:20,285
[in English] We're polishing
this bottle off pretty fast.

472
00:41:20,360 --> 00:41:23,762
Listen, I am not missing my flight
for anything tomorrow.

473
00:41:23,840 --> 00:41:25,410
Mmm?

474
00:41:26,200 --> 00:41:27,531
N0.

475
00:41:29,720 --> 00:41:31,404
You sure you can't stay?

